68-4fd9-be1f-29c2f58f8e39", "node_type": null, "metadata": {"Title_URL": "https://www.iucn.org/resources/grey-literature/desertas-wolf-spider-conservation-strategy-2016-2022", "Author": "International Union for Conservation of Nature", "Publisher": "International Union for Conservation of Nature", "Type": "Report"}, "hash": "c280cd8d2256baf1bb102f1d0991126d63204c320f0f21b3af9dbb3a12a2d215"}}, "hash": "71202204fc3c4770b38b529cbc8cc7126bab7517c661a7ce561b5cc0f737ffbc", "text": "Schedule: 2016 onwards iv. Resources: Staff time, same as ex-situ breeding v. Results: Exhibitions running with graphical interpretation, livecam and brochures produced DESERTAS WOLF SPIDER CONSERVATION PLAN 14 d) Media i. Responsible: IFCN ii. Actors: IFCN, BZS, IUCN iii. Schedule: 2016 onwards iv. Resources: Media partners v. Results: News, press releases Monitoring of effectiveness Actions will be monitored and objectives reviewed every year from 2016 to 2022. Annual reports will be produced. Compilation and dissemination of information will be made by IUCN - SSSG. Sites for action In-situ conservation will be done in the Castanheira Valley. Ex-situ conservation will be done at Bristol Zoological Gardens and possibly other European zoos. Timeline Action 2016 2017 2018 2019 2020 2021 2022 1a. Intervention 1b. Monitoring 1c. Plant reproduction 2a. Letter agreement 2b. Founder population 2c. Increased captures 2d. Develop management plan 2e. Run management plan 3a. PhD student 3b. Sub-population status 3c. Habitat preference 3d. Climate change 3e. In-situ experiments 4a. Website 4b. Video 4c. Zoo exhibitions 4d. Media DESERTAS WOLF SPIDER CONSERVATION PLAN 15 Actors The organisations and people involved in different actions and stages of the project will be: Institute of Forests and Conservation of Nature (IFCN). \uf0a7 Eng. Manuel Filipe (President of the Directive Council) \uf0a7 Dr. Paulo Oliveira (Vice-president of the Directive Council) \uf0a7 Eng. Duarte Barreto (Head of Biodiversity and 