48a16887075a93d1054405cd2"}}, "hash": "684a281bba39a04d9f140caa21c597992715d8b9a3ccddaa86cff7562e1c3195", "text": "\uf0a7 Cardoso, P. 2014. Hogna ingens. The IUCN Red List of Threatened Species. Version 2014.2. <www.iucnredlist.org>. Downloaded on 13 August 2014. \uf0a7 Crespo, L.C., Silva, I., Borges, P.A.V. and Cardoso, P. 2014. Assessing the conservation status of the strict endemic Desertas wolf spider, Hogna ingens (Araneae, Lycosidae). Journal for Nature Conservation, in press. \uf0a7 Denis, J. 1962. Les araign\u00e9es de l'archipel de Mad\u00e8re (Mission du Professeur Vandel). Publica\u00e7\u00f5es do Instituto de Zoologia Dr. Augusto Nobre 79: 1-118. \uf0a7 Ferreira, M.T., Cardoso, P., Borges, P.A.V., Gabriel, R., Azevedo, E.B., Reis, F., Ara\u00fajo, M.B. & Elias, R.B. 2016. Effects of climate change on the distribution of indigenous species in oceanic islands (Azores). Climatic Change, in press. \uf0a7 IUCN. 2014. The IUCN Red List of Threatened Species. Version 2014.2. Available at: www.iucnredlist.org. (Accessed: 24 July 2014). \uf0a7 Kulczynski, W. 1899. Arachnoidea opera Rev. Schmitz collecta in insulis Maderianis et Selvages dictis. Rozprawa i sprawodzanie wydziat matematyczno-pzyrodniczy Academia umiejetnosi Cracov 36: 319-461. \uf0a7 Roewer, C.F. 1960. Araneae Lycosaeformia II (Lycosidae) (Fortsetzung und Schluss). Exploration du Parc National de l\u2019Upemba. Mission G.F. de Witte 55: 519-1040. \uf0a7 Wunderlich, J. 1992. Die Spinnen-Fauna der Makaronesischen Inseln. Beitr\u00e4ge zur Araneologie 1: 1-619. DESERTAS WOLF SPIDER CONSERVATION PLAN 29 AGREEMENT The vision, goals and objectives of the Desertas Wolf Spider conservation strategy are shared by: Institute of Forests and Conservation of Nature Date: Signature: IUCN Species Survival Commission - Species Conservation Planning Sub-Committee Date: Signature: Bristol Zoological Society (BZS) Date: Signature: DESERTAS WOLF SPIDER CONSERVATION PLAN 30 Appendix I - Workshop schedule Monday 9 May 2016 09h30 Welcome and opening remarks 09h45 Presentations of participants 10h00 What is the IUCN, the SCP and the SSSG 10h45 Outlining the workshop 11h00 Coffee break 11h30 Biology and conservation of CR species 12h00 Vision 12h30 Lunch 14h00 Goals 14h30 Objectives 15h00 Conservation management in situ I 16h00 Coffee break 16h30 Conservation management in situ II 17h30 End of day 1 Tuesday 10 May 2016 09h30 Conservation management ex-situ 11h00 Coffee break 11h30 Legal protection 12h30 Lunch 14h00 Outreach 15h00 Funding options 16h30 Preparation and advice for field trip 17h30 End of workshop DESERTAS WOLF SPIDER CONSERVATION PLAN 31 Appendix II - Workshop notes Day 1 - May 9th 2016 10h00 - Opening remarks and personal presentations Miguel Sequeira", "start_char_idx": null, "end_char_idx": null, "text_template": "{metadata_str}\n\n{content}", "metadata_template": "{key}: {value}", "metadata_seperator": "\n"}, "__type__": "1"}, "0ede332c-4ad3-4700-b2b2-17844d343651": {"__data__": {"id_": "0ede332c-4ad3-4700-b2b2-17844d343651", "embedding": null, "metadata": {"Title_URL": "https://www.iucn.org/resources/grey-literature/desertas-wolf-spider-conservation-strategy-2016-2022", "Author": "International Union for Conservation of Nature", "Publisher": "International Union for Conservation of Nature", "Type": "Report"}, "excluded_embed_metadata_keys": [], "excluded_llm_metadata_keys": [], "relationships": {"1": {"node_id": "The Desertas wolf spider : conservation strategy 2016-2022", "node_type": null, "metadata": {"Title_URL": "https://www.iucn.org/resources/grey-literature/desertas-wolf-spider-conservation-strategy-2016-2022", "Author": "International Union for Conservation of Nature", "Publisher": "International Union for Conservation of Nature", "Type": "Report"}, "hash": "b6342e0ec49c2e26648906abddf46b7fdf33fc7ae8f1aa8a64b154366f760afe"}, "3": {"node_id": "fe4b1702-efb3-4fd1-889e-4cd1421a57e2", "node_type": null, "metadata": {"Title_URL": "https://www.iucn.org/resources/